
#  N.B. the previous line should be blank.
#+
#  Name:
#     pgp_link

#  Purpose:
#     Generate linker (ld) arguments for linking against standalone 
#        Starlink-PGPLOT.

#  Type of Module:
#     Shell script.

#  Description:
#     This script should be invoked by those building standalone
#     applications which use Starlink-PGPLOT in order to generate the correct
#     arguments for the compiler (or ld) command. The arguments
#     generated are written to the standard output.

#  Invocation:
#     The script is normally invoked as part of a compiler command line,
#     such as:
#
#        f77 -o program -L/star/lib `pgp_link` program.f

#  Copyright:
#     Copyright (C) 1995-1998 Rutherford Appleton Laboratory

#  Authors:
#     RFWS: R.F. Warren-Smith (STARLINK, RAL)
#     BLY:  M.J. Bly (Starlink, RAL)
#     DLT:  D.L. Terrett (Starlink, RAL)
#     {enter_new_authors_here}

#  History:
#     17-JUL-1995 (DLT):
#        Original version created from template.
#     23-SEP-1998 (BLY):
#        Renamed pgp_link for Starlink-PGPLOT.
#     {enter_further_changes_here}

#  Bugs:
#     {note_any_bugs_here}

#-

      echo -lpgp `psx_link` `gns_link` `err_link` `chr_link` `gks_link` \
           | awk 'BEGIN{RS=" ";FS="\n"}
                  {f[i++]=$1}
                  END{for(;i--;)if(!w[f[i]]++)l=f[i]" "l;print l}'

#  End of script.
